2Arithmetic Shifting Considered Harmful
.sp
.center
0by
.sp
.center
Guy L. Steele Jr. *
.sp 6
Abstract:
	For more than a decade there has been great confusion
over the semantics of the standard "arithmetic right shift"
instruction.  This confusion particularly afflicts authors
of computer reference handbooks and of optimizing compilers.
The fact that shifting is not always equivalent to division
has been rediscovered over and over again over the years,
but has never been publicized.
	This paper quotes a large number of sources
to prove the widespread extent of this confusion, and
then proceeds to a short discussion of the problem itself
and what to do about it.
.sp 3
.in 6
.un 6
Keywords:  arithmetic shift, twos complement, ones complement, division,
remainder, binary arithmetic
